curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/3713' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM42633", "table_name": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION", "content": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION  The SGM42633 is a motor driver device with two  integrated H-bridges that can run a bipolar stepper  motor. The device can operate over a wide input  voltage range of 2.5V to 12V, and each H-bridge of the  SGM42633 can deliver up to 700mA RMS (or DC)  continuously (at VCC = 5V, TJ = +25℃).  Internal over-current and over-temperature circuits  prevent the device from being in over-stress condition,  while a fault output simplifies stalling sensing, which is  a useful feature for most applications. Aiming for  battery-powered applications, it can go into low-power  mode for increased battery life.  The device is available in Green TQFN-3×3-16L and  TSSOP-16 (Exposed Pad) packages.     "}'
